# .env.example — committed source of truth for kind-cluster operator tunables.
#
# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and edit to override without touching the Makefile:
#     cp .env.example .env
# The Makefile `-include .env`s this before its `?=` defaults, so a value here
# wins for `make` targets; scripts read the same names via `${VAR:-default}`.
# Every value below is the built-in default — uncomment + change only what you
# need. All are deployment knobs (this lab runs no long-lived service, so there
# are no host/port/credential runtime tunables to externalize).

# --- Cluster identity -------------------------------------------------------
# KinD cluster + kubeconfig context name (context is `kind-$KIND_CLUSTER_NAME`).
# Override to coexist with another KinD project on the same workstation.
# KIND_CLUSTER_NAME=kind

# LoadBalancer provider for `make install-all`: empty/unset = cloud-provider-kind
# (default); `metallb` = MetalLB. Equivalent to `make install-all LB=metallb`.
# LB=

# --- Local dev registry (`make registry`) -----------------------------------
# Host port the local registry binds (127.0.0.1:$REGISTRY_PORT -> registry:5000).
# Change it if 5001 is already taken on the host.
# REGISTRY_PORT=5001

# --- Host ports -------------------------------------------------------------
# Host-side ingress ports (templated into kind's extraPortMappings) + the
# Headlamp port-forward local port. Change any that collide with a host process
# or a second cluster; `make check-ports` names the holder of a bound port.
INGRESS_HTTP_PORT=80
INGRESS_HTTPS_PORT=443
HEADLAMP_LOCAL_PORT=8081

# --- Startup polling (optional overrides) -----------------------------------
# Override EVERY startup poll loop at once (readiness / route-readiness waits).
# Leave unset so each loop keeps its own tuned default via ${POLL_ATTEMPTS:-N}.
# POLL_ATTEMPTS=
# POLL_INTERVAL=

# --- Host-side NFS (`make nfs-host-provisioner`) ----------------------------
# IP of the host running nfs-kernel-server (no default — required for that target).
# NFS_SERVER=
# Exported NFS path on that host (defaults to the provisioner script's default).
# NFS_PATH=

# --- Multipass VM (`make vm-up` / `vm-*`) -----------------------------------
# VM name and size. Defaults come from scripts/vm-up.sh (kind-host / 4 / 8G / 40G).
# NAME=kind-host
# CPUS=4
# MEMORY=8G
# DISK=40G

# --- e2e smoke assertions (scripts/e2e-smoke.sh; optional overrides) ---------
# Grafana admin username for the TEST_MONITORING login proof (the password is
# read from the cluster secret, never set here).
# GRAFANA_ADMIN_USER=admin
# Host header used by the TEST_GATEWAY_API Kong classic-Ingress assertion.
# KONG_INGRESS_HOST=helloweb.kong-ingress.localdev.me
